problem_statement:
Control all FHIR interactions via AccessPolicy
Currently, Medplum's `AccessPolicy` resource type allow coarse-grained read-write control via a boolean field:

```ts
{
  resourceType: 'AccessPolicy',
  resource: [
    { resourceType: 'Observation', readonly: true }
  ]
}
```

However, users need more fine-grained access control, and should be able to specify individual [FHIR interactions](http://hl7.org/fhir/valueset-type-restful-interaction.html) that are allowed (e.g. `create`, `delete`, `search`).  This can be represented in the AccessPolicy in a backwards-compatible way:

```ts
{
  resourceType: 'AccessPolicy',
  resource: [
    // Old way
    { resourceType: 'Observation', readonly: true },
    // New way
    { resourceType: 'Observation', interactions: ['read', 'search'] }
  ]
}
```

Internally, when [constructing the synthetic AccessPolicy](https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/bb84134ecf7cc4c6edeac8658e235fefa9baf6dd/packages/server/src/fhir/accesspolicy.ts#L85) to use during a server request, we should translate all `AccessPolicy.resource` entries to use the new format via the following conversion:

| `readonly` | `interactions` |
| --- | --- |
| `false` or `undefined` | `['create', 'read', 'update', 'delete', 'search']` |
| `true` | `['read', 'search']` |

First, `matchesAccessPolicyResourcePolicy()` in `@medplum/core` will need to be updated to handle the new case, where the interaction can be directly checked against the `AccessPolicy.resource.interaction` value(s).

This will also require updating code throughout the server to honor the more comprehensive checks; namely, the logic in `packages/server/fhir/repo.ts` should call `satisfiedAccessPolicy` with the correct interaction in all locations where interactions take place

