problem_statement:
Medplum returns `Invalid format for date search parameter `when using `pr` operator on `dateTime`
## Description

@filipeximenes is trying to use the `pr` (presence) operator on a `dateTime` attribute in Medplum, specifically with the `Communication` resource type. However, when attempting the query, the following error message is returned: `Invalid format for date search parameter: false`

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/58f1275b-b4ee-4d31-8c59-0aeecdc7fc6a)

### Expected Behavior

The query should successfully return results for `pr=true` or `pr=false` based on the presence of the `sent` `dateTime` field in the `Communication` resource. The `pr` operator should indicate whether the attribute is present or not without returning an invalid format error.

### Actual Behavior

The query returns an invalid format error: `Invalid format for date search parameter: false`, which prevents any results from being returned.

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Attempt to query a `Communication` resource using the `pr` operator on a `dateTime` attribute
```ts
const query = `{
  CommunicationList(_filter: "_has:Task:based-on:due-date pr true") {
    id,
    resourceType
  }
}`;
await medplum.graphql(query);
```

2. Notice that the query returns an error: `Invalid format for date search parameter: false`

## Related Resources

- [Comparison Operators](https://www.medplum.com/docs/search/filter-search-parameter#comparison-operators)

