problem_statement:
Enable call-time auto-batch opt-out for MedplumClient
## Description
Currently, when a `MedplumClient` is initialized with auto-batching enabled (via `autoBatchTime`), all eligible GET requests to the FHIR API are automatically batched. However, there are cases where users may want to opt-out of auto-batching for specific GET requests while keeping the general auto-batching behavior enabled.

## Proposed Solution
Add a new option specific to GET requests by extending the base `MedplumRequestOptions`:

```typescript
export interface MedplumGetRequestOptions extends MedplumRequestOptions {
  /**
   * Optional flag to disable auto-batching for this specific request.
   * Only applies when the client is configured with auto-batching enabled.
   */
  disableAutoBatch?: boolean;
}

// Update relevant method signatures to use the new options
export interface MedplumClient {
  readResource<K extends ResourceType>(
    resourceType: K,
    id: string,
    options?: MedplumGetRequestOptions
  ): Promise<ExtractResource<K>>;
  
  search<K extends ResourceType>(
    resourceType: K,
    query?: Record<string, string | string[]> | URLSearchParams | undefined,
    options?: MedplumGetRequestOptions
  ): Promise<Bundle<ExtractResource<K>>>;
  
  // ... other FHIR GET methods
}
```

Example usage:
```typescript
// Client initialized with auto-batching
const medplum = new MedplumClient({ 
  autoBatchTime: 100 
});

// Normal auto-batched request
await medplum.readResource('Patient', '123');

// Opt out of auto-batching for specific request
await medplum.readResource('Patient', '456', {
  disableAutoBatch: true
});
```

## Implementation Details
1. Create new `MedplumGetRequestOptions` interface extending `MedplumRequestOptions`
2. Update signatures of GET methods to use the new options type
3. Modify the `get()` method to check for this flag before adding to auto-batch queue:

```typescript
if (url.startsWith(this.fhirBaseUrl) && this.autoBatchQueue && !options.disableAutoBatch) {
  // ... existing auto-batch logic ...
}
```

## Benefits
- Provides more granular control over auto-batching behavior
- Maintains clean inheritance from base request options
- Better TypeScript type safety by making the option only available for GET requests
- Maintains backward compatibility

## Related Issues/PRs
- None

## Additional Context
This feature would be particularly useful in scenarios where:
- Certain GET requests need immediate execution
- Debugging specific API calls
- Performance optimization for time-sensitive operations

