problem_statement:
`Bundle.entry` without a `fullUrl` incorrectly fails validation
When attempting to create a `Bundle` resource with an `entry` without `fullUrl` like:
```ts
{
  "resourceType": "Bundle",
  "type": "searchset",
  "entry": [
    {
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Patient"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

We get a violation of constraint `bdl-8` (see: https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/bundle.html#invs):
`fullUrl.contains('/_history/').not()`

This constraint in R4 conflicts with the optional cardinality of `fullUrl`, however this was fixed in R5 with an update to `bdl-8` (see: https://hl7.org/fhir/R5/bundle.html#invs):
`fullUrl.exists() implies fullUrl.contains('/_history/').not()`

We should backport this change to `bdl-8` so that a `Bundle.entry` without `fullUrl` doesn't cause validation to fail.

